<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7652&amp;p=78055#p78055"><![CDATA[
Actually, you should divide the number of samples per second (44100) by the refresh rate (around 60hz), in order to get the number of samples per sync (735), and not the reverse, ever.<br /><br />For Allegro, I use 2048 bytes (times 2 for stereo sound) as buffer. Then, you divide the number of CPU cycles per second (hardware clock) by the PC sample rate (44100).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=39">Zepper</a> — Wed May 11, 2011 5:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
