<title type="html"><![CDATA[I give up, I can't find a way to emulate chiptune sound!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7652&amp;p=77766#p77766"><![CDATA[
Ok, I rushed on back home to get the files I need to show you guys how far I've come along so you can help me better. <br /><br /><a href="http://www.megaupload.com/?d=LZ65IKD5" class="postlink">My sound test on the NES</a>:<br /><br />Up and Down: Move cursor up and down<br />Left and Right: Increment or Decrement the value of the currently selected option<br />B: Move to a different channel<br />A: Play the Sound<br /><br /><img src="http://i72.photobucket.com/albums/i175/Undubbed/NES_Sound_Test.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Here's a picture of my Wave Analyzer, but I'm not sure if I should upload that one just yet.<br /><br /><img src="http://i72.photobucket.com/albums/i175/Undubbed/WaveAnalyzer.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Last, but not least, a picture of my Sound Test - Host Edition<br /><br />All it does right now is play the wave based on the wavelength given under the Fine/Coarse tab. Not uploading this either, unless someone really wants to see it<br /><img src="http://i72.photobucket.com/albums/i175/Undubbed/Sound_Test_Picture.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><br />Now for the actual code. Here what I have for the Square Wave in my Sound Test - Host Edition program.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Imports Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Audio<br /><br />Public MustInherit Class NesWave<br />    Protected _audio_stream As DynamicSoundEffectInstance<br />    Protected _buffer&#40;&#41; As Byte<br /><br />    Protected sample_rate As Double<br />    Protected samples As Double<br /><br />    Public MustOverride Sub Play&#40;&#41;<br />End Class</div><br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Imports Microsoft.Xna.Framework.Audio<br /><br />Public Class SquareWave<br />    ' must implement Play&#40;&#41;<br />    Inherits NesWave<br /><br />    Private _vol As Integer<br />    Private _env As Boolean<br />    Private _lcc_dis As Boolean<br />    Private _duty_cycle As Double<br /><br />    Private _right_shift As Integer<br />    Private _sweep_update As Integer<br />    Private _inc_dec_wavelength As Boolean<br />    Private _sweep_enable As Boolean<br />    Private _wavelength As Integer<br />    Private _length_counter As Integer<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />    Public Sub New&#40;ByVal sampleRate As Double, ByVal samples As Double, ByVal chan As AudioChannels&#41;<br />        _audio_stream = New DynamicSoundEffectInstance&#40;sampleRate, chan&#41;<br />        Me.sample_rate = sampleRate<br />        Me.samples = samples<br /><br />    End Sub<br />    Public Overrides Sub Play&#40;&#41;<br />        Dim freq As Double = NES_Wavelength_to_Freq&#40;Wavelength&#41;<br /><br />        Dim w As Double = &#40;2 * Math.PI&#41; * freq<br /><br />        Dim ti As Double<br />        Dim y As Double<br />        Dim dt As Double = 1 / sample_rate<br /><br />        Dim wave_buffer&#40;samples - 1&#41; As Double<br /><br />        ReDim _buffer&#40;&#40;samples * 2&#41; - 1&#41;<br /><br />        For i = 0 To wave_buffer.Length - 1<br />            ti = i * dt<br />            y = Math.Sin&#40;w * ti&#41;<br /><br />            If y &gt;= 0.0 Then<br />                y = 1.0<br />            Else<br />                y = -1.0<br />            End If<br /><br />            wave_buffer&#40;i&#41; = y<br />        Next<br />        <br />        ' Convert from Wave format to PCM format that XNA accpets<br />        ConvertBuffer&#40;wave_buffer, _buffer&#41;<br />        _audio_stream.SubmitBuffer&#40;_buffer&#41;<br />        _audio_stream.Play&#40;&#41;<br />    End Sub<br /><br />   ' Irrelevant property declarations was here<br />End Class<br /></div><br /><br /><br />My Duty Cycle idea is implemented in my Wave Analyzer and I suspect that I can just do the same thing in my Sound Test, with a little adjustment. Also I'm about to do envelope but it hasn't actually been implemented beyond variable declaration. <br /><br />I think I need to desperately separate sine wave implementations and square wave into 2 classes derived from a wave base, but I hope it's still readable.<br /><br />Anywayz, the idea for duty cycle is that you take the sample period and divide it using the Duty Cycle value into a positve part and a negative part. Make a positive loop that goes from 0 to the amount of posive samples in the period. Then it continues from that to the sample period for negative. Seems like the wave comes out just fine for any Duty Cycle you input, but maybe someone has a better algorithm?<br /><br /><br />Duty Cycle 12.5%<br /><img src="http://i72.photobucket.com/albums/i175/Undubbed/DutyCycle_125.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Duty Cycle 25%<br /><img src="http://i72.photobucket.com/albums/i175/Undubbed/DutyCycle_25.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Duty Cycle 50%<br /><img src="http://i72.photobucket.com/albums/i175/Undubbed/DutyCycle_50.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Duty Cycle 25% negated<br /><img src="http://i72.photobucket.com/albums/i175/Undubbed/DutyCycle_25_negated.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Luckily it's just one file for the entire program (Sound Test has many irrelevant files for other waves and stuff). Wave algorithm for square is under the Button1_Click event function<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Imports System.Convert<br />Imports ZedGraph<br /><br /><br />Public Class Wave_Editor<br /><br />    Private dt As New Double<br />    Private SquareWave_On As Boolean = False<br /><br />    Private Sub Form1_Load&#40;ByVal sender As System.Object, ByVal e As System.EventArgs&#41; Handles MyBase.Load<br />        Samples.Value = Sample_Frequency.Value / 60<br />        dt = 1.0 / Sample_Frequency.Value<br />    End Sub<br /><br />    Private Sub Frequency_ValueChanged&#40;ByVal sender As System.Object, ByVal e As System.EventArgs&#41; Handles Frequency.ValueChanged<br />        'Sample size must be at the minimum specified or else non of the complete wave will show<br />        Dim minimum As Integer = &#40;Sample_Frequency.Value / Frequency.Value&#41;<br />        If Samples.Value &lt; minimum Then<br />            Samples.Value = minimum<br />        End If<br />    End Sub<br /><br />    Private Sub Samples_ValueChanged&#40;ByVal sender As System.Object, ByVal e As System.EventArgs&#41; Handles Samples.ValueChanged<br />    End Sub<br /><br />    Private Sub Phase_ValueChanged&#40;ByVal sender As System.Object, ByVal e As System.EventArgs&#41; Handles Phase.ValueChanged<br /><br />    End Sub<br /><br />    Private Sub Button1_Click&#40;ByVal sender As System.Object, ByVal e As System.EventArgs&#41; Handles Button1.Click<br /><br />        Dim x&#40;Samples.Value - 1&#41; As Double<br />        Dim y&#40;Samples.Value - 1&#41; As Double<br />        Dim w As Double = &#40;&#40;2 * Math.PI&#41; * Frequency.Value&#41;<br /><br /><br />        If Sine_Wave_Toggle.Checked Then<br />            For sample_index = 0 To Samples.Value<br />                ' dt is the location of the sample in time<br />                ' multiplied by the index I can move on to the next sample in time<br />                ' end result gives the x value needed<br />                x&#40;sample_index&#41; = sample_index * dt<br /><br />                ' y will be the amplitude output of the sine wave function<br />                y&#40;sample_index&#41; = Math.Sin&#40;w * x&#40;sample_index&#41;&#41;<br />            Next sample_index<br /><br />        ElseIf Square_Wave_Toggle.Checked Then<br />            ' Following variables are used to calculate the duty cycle<br />            ' Using the samples, not the wave itself<br />            Dim T As Integer = Sample_Frequency.Value / Frequency.Value<br />            Dim dc As Double = Duty_Cycle.Value * 0.01<br />            Dim amp As Double<br /><br />            If Duty_Cycle_Negated.Checked Then<br />                amp = -1.0<br />            Else<br />                amp = 1.0<br />            End If<br /><br />            ' Envelope variables<br />            Dim samples_per_cycle As Integer = Sample_Frequency.Value / Samples.Value<br />            Dim envelope_decay_rate As Integer = 240 / &#40;Envelope.Value + 1&#41;<br />            Dim samples_per_envelope_decay As Integer = samples_per_cycle * envelope_decay_rate<br />            Dim envelope_volume&#40;&amp;HF&#41; As Single<br />            For i = 0 To UBound&#40;envelope_volume&#41;<br />                ' 6.25% is 1/16th volume<br />                envelope_volume&#40;i&#41; = i * 0.0625<br />            Next<br /><br />            Dim sample_period As Integer = Sample_Frequency.Value / Frequency.Value<br /><br />            For sample_index = 0 To UBound&#40;x&#41; Step sample_period<br /><br />                For positive_period = 0 To Math.Floor&#40;&#40;sample_period * dc&#41;&#41; - 1<br />                    Dim index As Integer = sample_index + positive_period<br />                    If index &gt;= x.Length Then<br />                        Exit For<br />                    End If<br />                    x&#40;index&#41; = index * dt<br />                    y&#40;index&#41; = amp<br />                Next positive_period<br /><br />                For negative_period = Math.Floor&#40;&#40;sample_period * dc&#41;&#41; To sample_period - 1<br />                    Dim index As Integer = sample_index + negative_period<br /><br />                    'Jump out early if it reaches the end of the array<br />                    ' since the period the sample size doesn't always<br />                    ' divide evenly<br />                    If index &gt;= x.Length Then<br />                        Exit For<br />                    End If<br /><br />                    x&#40;index&#41; = index * dt<br />                    y&#40;index&#41; = -amp<br />                Next negative_period<br /><br />            Next sample_index<br /><br />        End If<br /><br />        'This is to remove all plots<br />        ZedGraphControl1.GraphPane.CurveList.Clear&#40;&#41;<br /><br />        'GraphPane object holds one or more Curve objects &#40;or plots&#41;<br />        Dim myPane As GraphPane = ZedGraphControl1.GraphPane<br />        myPane.XAxis.Title.Text = &quot;Time&quot;<br />        myPane.YAxis.Title.Text = &quot;Amp&quot;<br /><br />        'PointPairList holds the data for plotting, X and Y arrays<br />        Dim spl1 As PointPairList = New PointPairList&#40;x, y&#41;<br /><br /><br />        'Add cruves to myPane object<br />        Dim myCurve1 As LineItem = myPane.AddCurve&#40;&quot;Sine Wave&quot;, spl1, Color.Blue, SymbolType.None&#41;<br /><br />        myCurve1.Line.Width = 3.0F<br />        myPane.Title.Text = &quot;Sine Wave Analyze&quot;<br /><br />        'I add all three functions just to be sure it refeshes the plot.  <br />        ZedGraphControl1.AxisChange&#40;&#41;<br />        ZedGraphControl1.Invalidate&#40;&#41;<br />        ZedGraphControl1.Refresh&#40;&#41;<br />    End Sub<br /><br />    Private Sub Sample_Frequency_ValueChanged&#40;ByVal sender As System.Object, ByVal e As System.EventArgs&#41; Handles Sample_Frequency.ValueChanged<br />        dt = 1 / Sample_Frequency.Value<br />        Samples.Value = Sample_Frequency.Value / 60<br />    End Sub<br />End Class<br /></div><br /><br /><br />Hopefully all this junk I posted can give you guys a good idea on how much I know and/or don't know. Thanks for your time!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4007">Undubbed</a> — Fri May 06, 2011 1:40 pm</p><hr />
